Phase 1: MVP (Core Functionality)
 Install Command (suffer install <github-url>)

 Parse GitHub URL
 Clone repo to temp location
 Extract lib name from URL or repo
 Detect dependencies:

 Check for existing suffer.json
 Parse CMakeLists.txt for find_package()
 Prompt user if cant detect


 Generate suffer.json for lib
 Move to registry
 Verify git is installed

Import

 Resolve dependencies recursively
 Check build cache (~/.suffer/cache/)
 Build lib if not cached:

 Compile source files
 Create static archive (.a)
 Bundle dependencies (static linking)


 Copy headers to lib/include/
 Copy static lib to lib/static/
 Update suffer.json with dependency
 Update suffer.lock with versions/commits
 Regenerate Makefile

 Builder System

 Detect if lib is header-only
 Compile .c/.cpp files to .o
 Create static archive with ar
 Merge dependency .a files (static linking)
 Handle build errors gracefully
 Parallel compilation support (future)


 Cache System (~/.suffer/cache/)

 Hash source files for cache key
 Include dependency versions in cache key
 Store built .a files
 cache.json metadata
 Cache invalidation on source changes



Phase 3: Configuration

 Config Command (suffer config)

 suffer config set standard c++20
 suffer config set flags "-Wall -O3"
 suffer config set compiler clang++
 suffer config set defines "DEBUG_MODE"
 suffer config list - show current settings
 Update sufferSettings.json
 Regenerate Makefile after changes


 VSCode Integration

 Generate .vscode/c_cpp_properties.json
 Auto-include lib/include in includePath
 Match compiler settings from sufferSettings.json



Phase 4: Polish

 CLI Interface

 Proper argument parsing
 --help for all commands
 --version flag
 Colored output (optional, not ncurses)
 Progress indicators for long operations


 Error Handling

 Validate GitHub URLs
 Check for git installation
 Handle network failures
 Handle corrupt archives
 Helpful error messages
 Rollback on failed imports


 Build Command (suffer build)

 Wrapper around make
 Show compilation progress
 Handle build errors


 Remove Command (suffer remove <lib>)

 Remove from lib/
 Update suffer.json
 Regenerate Makefile



Phase 5: Distribution (Future)

 Package Command (suffer package)

 suffer package appimage

 Generate AppDir structure
 Create .desktop file
 Run appimagetool


 suffer package flatpak

 Generate Flatpak manifest
 Run flatpak-builder


 Accept flags: --name, --icon, --version



